## 2. Core Interaction Pattern

### Hover Card + Slide-Out Sidebar

This interaction pattern is the **universal UI standard** applied across every watch box interface in the product — My Collection, Playground Mode, Saved Views, and any shared or embedded box.

**How it works:**

1. **Hover** — Hovering over any watch slot surfaces a compact floating card above the slot containing:
   - Brand name
   - Watch name
   - Reference number
   - Case size
   - Estimated market value
   - A subtle "Click to expand ↗" prompt

2. **Click** — Clicking a watch slot slides open a persistent right-hand sidebar with full watch detail:
   - Dial visualization
   - Complete spec sheet (case size, material, dial color, movement, complications)
   - Ownership data (condition, purchase date, price paid)
   - Estimated current market value
   - Quick action buttons: **Find For Sale ↗**, **Sell This Watch**, **Swap Strap**

3. **Dismiss** — Clicking the same slot again, or the ✕ button, collapses the sidebar and returns to the full box view.

**Design rules:**
- The hover card floats above the hovered slot and never obscures adjacent slots
- The sidebar slides in from the right without pushing or reflowing the box grid
- Only one sidebar can be open at a time; clicking a different watch swaps the content in place without a full close/reopen
- Empty slots show an "Add Watch" state on hover — no card, just a `+` CTA
- The active slot is visually highlighted with a gold border accent while its sidebar is open

**Applies to all watch box interfaces:**
- Feature 1 — Virtual Watch Box Display (My Collection)
- Feature 4 — Playground Mode & Saved Views
- Feature 8 — Virtual Try-On Room (watch selection panel)
- Any publicly shared or embedded box view

