### Feature 2 — My Collection (Watch Detail Sidebar)

The slide-out sidebar is the primary detail surface for My Collection. It is triggered by clicking any watch slot in the box (per the Core Interaction Pattern in Section 2) and gives the user a full view of that watch's metadata, ownership history, and quick actions — without navigating away from the box.

**User Stories**
- As a user, I want to click a watch in my box and instantly see all its details in a sidebar so I never lose context of my full collection.
- As a collector, I want to record purchase date, price paid, and estimated current value for insurance and tracking purposes.
- As a user, I want to add personal notes to each watch (e.g., "Gift from dad, 2018").

**Functional Requirements**
- Sidebar slides in from the right on watch slot click (see Section 2)
- Sidebar displays: dial visualization, brand, full reference number, case size (mm), case material, dial color, movement, complications
- Ownership fields (editable): purchase date, purchase price, condition, notes
- Condition displayed as a color-coded badge (Unworn, Like New, Excellent, Good, Fair)
- Estimated market value displayed prominently, pulled from WatchCharts / Chrono24 API or manually entered
- Quick action buttons: **Find For Sale ↗**, **Sell This Watch**, **Swap Strap**
- Clicking a different slot swaps sidebar content in place — no full close/reopen animation
- ✕ button or second click on active slot dismisses sidebar

**MVP Scope**
- Sidebar with manually entered metadata
- Dial SVG visualization
- Condition badge, purchase details, estimated value display
- Three quick action buttons (wired in later phases)

| Feature | Description | Priority |
|---|---|---|
| Slide-Out Sidebar | Triggered by slot click, dismissible via ✕ or re-click | P0 – Must Have |
| Dial Visualization | SVG watch face rendered per watch in the sidebar | P0 – Must Have |
| Watch Metadata | Full spec display (brand, ref, size, complications) | P0 – Must Have |
| Condition Badge | Color-coded condition indicator | P0 – Must Have |
| Editable Fields | Purchase price, date, notes, condition | P1 – High |
| Quick Actions | Find For Sale, Sell, Swap Strap buttons | P1 – High |
| Live Value Data | Pull estimated value from Chrono24 / WatchCharts | P2 – Medium |

