### Feature 3 — Advanced Watch Search & Selection

A powerful, filter-driven search experience modeled on luxury car configurators. Users can find any watch from a curated database using attributes like brand, complications, case size, color, and price range.

**User Stories**
- As a user, I want to search watches like I search for a car — by brand, style, size, and feature — so I can find exactly what I'm looking for.
- As a user, I want live search results with thumbnail previews so I can visually evaluate options before adding them.

**Functional Requirements**
- Search bar with type-ahead suggestions
- Filter panel: brand, case size (mm), movement type, complication (chronograph, moonphase, GMT, tourbillon, etc.), strap type, case material, dial color, price range, year
- Results grid with thumbnail, brand, model name, reference, and price indicator
- Selecting a result places watch into the active box slot
- Data sourced from WatchBase API and/or a curated internal database

**MVP Scope**
- Text search against a curated database of 500+ popular references
- 3–4 filter options (brand, size, complication, color)
- Grid results with image and basic spec

| Feature | Description | Priority |
|---|---|---|
| Text Search | Type-ahead search across brand/model/reference | P0 – Must Have |
| Filter Panel | Multi-attribute filter (brand, size, complication, etc.) | P0 – Must Have |
| Visual Results | Thumbnail + spec preview in results grid | P1 – High |
| Database Coverage | 500+ references at launch, scaled via API | P1 – High |
| Add to Slot | One-click add from search results to active slot | P0 – Must Have |

