### Feature 5 — Strap Customization & Matchmaking

Users can virtually swap straps on any watch in their box, with the system ensuring compatibility (lug width, attachment type) and offering curated purchase links for compatible straps.

**User Stories**
- As a collector, I want to see how a green NATO strap looks on my Submariner without buying it first.
- As a user, I want the platform to only show me straps that are actually compatible with my watch's lug width.
- As a user, I want a link to buy the strap I'm previewing.

**Functional Requirements**
- Strap swap UI: picker with material, color, and style filters
- Compatibility filtering by lug width (e.g., 18mm, 20mm, 22mm) and attachment type (standard, integrated, deployant)
- Visual preview: watch image updates in real time to reflect the selected strap
- Strap catalog with high-res images, descriptions, and affiliate purchase links
- Compatible strap suggestions based on watch style and user preferences
- Strap brands: NATO, Rubber B, Hirsch, Crown & Buckle, Wolf1834, and others via Etsy/Amazon affiliate

**MVP Scope**
- Strap picker for manually entered lug widths
- 4–6 strap style presets with visual overlay
- Static affiliate links for 2–3 strap suppliers

| Feature | Description | Priority |
|---|---|---|
| Strap Picker UI | Visual picker for material, color, style | P0 – Must Have |
| Compatibility Filter | Only show compatible straps by lug width | P0 – Must Have |
| Real-Time Preview | Watch image updates with selected strap | P1 – High |
| Purchase Links | Affiliate-linked strap buy buttons | P1 – High |
| Smart Suggestions | AI-curated strap recommendations per watch | P2 – Medium |

