### Feature 7 — Upload from Photo & Image Recognition

Users can upload a photo of a watch — from their camera roll or the internet — and the system uses image recognition to identify the model, match it to a reference in the database, and suggest where to buy it.

**User Stories**
- As a user scrolling Instagram, I want to snap a photo of a watch I see on someone's wrist and instantly find out what it is.
- As a collector, I want to photograph my watches and have the platform auto-populate their details.

**Functional Requirements**
- Upload interface: drag-and-drop or camera/gallery picker
- AI image recognition matches uploaded photo to brand, model, and reference
- Top 3–5 match results shown with confidence score, spec preview, and buy links
- Option to add matched watch directly to My Collection or Playground
- Handles multiple angles: dial-forward, wrist shot, flat lay
- Fallback: manual search if match is below confidence threshold

**MVP Scope**
- Single photo upload with Google Vision AI or Amazon Rekognition
- Top 3 match candidates displayed
- Add-to-collection button on match result

| Feature | Description | Priority |
|---|---|---|
| Photo Upload UI | Camera roll and URL upload interface | P1 – High |
| Image Recognition | AI model matching via Google Vision / Rekognition | P1 – High |
| Match Results | Top 3–5 candidates with confidence and specs | P1 – High |
| Add to Collection | One-click add from match result | P1 – High |
| Multi-Angle Handling | Handles dial, wrist, and flat-lay orientations | P2 – Medium |

