### Feature 8 — Virtual Try-On Room

Users upload a photo of their wrist or full outfit to see how a specific watch looks on them, with AI-assisted sizing, placement, and style matching.

**User Stories**
- As a buyer considering a 41mm watch, I want to see if it will look oversized on my 6.5" wrist before spending $5,000.
- As a fashion-conscious collector, I want to preview whether a gold Datejust complements my outfit before wearing it to an event.

**Functional Requirements**
- Photo upload: wrist/forearm, full body, or outfit flat lay
- AI wrist detection: identifies wrist region and overlays watch at correct scale
- Reference object for scale calibration (e.g., credit card held next to wrist)
- Watch sizing simulation: estimates if watch will appear proportionate based on wrist size estimate
- Strap and color variant swapping within the try-on view
- Outfit style check: tags the outfit context and suggests watch style matches
- Shareable try-on image with social share or A/B vote option
- CTA overlay: "Buy This Watch" and "Swap Strap" buttons in the try-on view

**MVP Scope**
- Manual overlay: user positions and scales watch on uploaded wrist photo
- 3–4 watch variants selectable in the try-on view
- Save and share try-on image

| Feature | Description | Priority |
|---|---|---|
| Photo Upload | Wrist or outfit photo input | P1 – High |
| Manual Overlay | User-positioned watch overlay with scale handles | P1 – High |
| AI Wrist Detection | Auto-placement via computer vision | P2 – Medium |
| Sizing Simulation | Proportionality estimate based on wrist measurement | P2 – Medium |
| Strap Swap in Try-On | Switch straps within the try-on view | P2 – Medium |
