### Feature 10 — Integrated Buying, Selling & Listing

Users can explore buying opportunities, list watches for sale on third-party platforms, and receive AI-assisted pricing suggestions — all without leaving Virtual Watchbox.

**User Stories**
- As a collector, I want to see live listings for a watch I'm interested in and be taken directly to the seller's page.
- As a seller, I want the platform to suggest a fair price for my watch based on comparable recent sales.
- As a user wanting to sell on Reddit Watch Exchange, I want a pre-populated post template so I don't have to write it from scratch.

**Functional Requirements**
- Buy flow: "Find This Watch for Sale" links out to Chrono24, WatchBox, eBay with affiliate tracking
- Live listings widget showing current price range for a reference (Chrono24 API)
- Sell flow: "Sell This Watch" button on each watch in My Collection
  - AI pricing suggestion based on reference, condition, year, and market comps (WatchCharts API)
  - Pre-filled listing template: title, description, specs, condition, asking price
  - One-click post to Chrono24, eBay, WatchRecon, or copy-paste for Reddit r/WatchExchange
- Condition selector: Unworn, Like New, Excellent, Good, Fair
- Include/exclude box and papers toggle
- Image upload for sale listing (reuse existing collection photos)

**MVP Scope**
- Affiliate deep-links to Chrono24 and eBay for buy flow
- Basic sell form with manual price entry and listing template generator
- Copy-to-clipboard for Reddit listing format

